        <p data-uuid="f15a4ed58803484da44627628736a940">At a press conference on
            October 22, Kennedy demanded that the Soviet Union remove the missiles. During
            the <b><dfn title="Cuban missile crisis">Cuban missile crisis</dfn></b>, the
            U.S. Navy formed a blockade around Cuba. The blockade was designed to prevent
            Soviet ships from bringing in more weapons. As Soviet ships approached the
            blockade, terrified Americans waited tensely for news updates. Then came some
            welcome news—the Soviet ships had turned back.</p>
