        <p data-uuid="cadc38c86b3f4a08995703fc7f58f916">After the crisis ended,
            Khrushchev agreed to remove the nuclear missiles from Cuba. In return, Kennedy
            promised not to invade Cuba. He also agreed to remove some missiles in Italy
            and Turkey. To improve future communication, Kennedy and Khrushchev set up a
            telephone “hotline” so the leaders could talk directly to each other at a
            moment’s notice. They also signed the Limited Nuclear Test Ban Treaty, which
            banned the testing of new nuclear weapons aboveground.</p>
